    "description": "<p><span style=\"font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', 'Lucida Sans Unicode', 'Lucida Grande', 'Lucida Sans', Arial, sans-serif\">You learn 2 Monk Stances from the list below.</span></p><ul><li><p>@UUID[Compendium.dc20rpg.classes.Item.WvOSzsxyZT42SUnZ]{Bear Stance (Big Hits)}</p></li><li><p>@UUID[Compendium.dc20rpg.classes.Item.AgcXozynq9SoFHnD]{Bull Stance (Knockback)}</p></li><li><p>@UUID[Compendium.dc20rpg.classes.Item.UgdB8O2JoyK4NqgB]{Cobra Stance (Counter)}</p></li><li><p>@UUID[Compendium.dc20rpg.classes.Item.bB9NFmpDv3rdpC8z]{Gazelle Stance (Nimble)}</p></li><li><p>@UUID[Compendium.dc20rpg.classes.Item.FLvjwuMeKtZtr0DA]{Mantis Stance (Grapple)}</p></li><li><p>@UUID[Compendium.dc20rpg.classes.Item.KO9jMTfGasOIS74C]{Mongoose Stance (Multi)}</p></li><li><p>@UUID[Compendium.dc20rpg.classes.Item.8bnkySEo8OwkWZ9C]{Scorpion Stance (Quick Strike)}</p></li><li><p>@UUID[Compendium.dc20rpg.classes.Item.pKz2jGXmTSx8YLV9]{Turtle Stance (Sturdy)}</p></li><li><p>@UUID[Compendium.dc20rpg.classes.Item.ZDFNR3ZVnorLlC4I]{Wolf Stance (Hit & Run)}</p></li></ul><p><strong>Entering & Exiting:</strong> In Combat at the start of each of your turns you can freely enter or swap into one of your Monk Stances. You can also spend <strong>1 SP</strong> on your turn to swap to a different stance. You can end your Stance at any moment for free. You can only be in 1 Monk Stance at a time.</p>",
